DRC Exam Proctoring Form for Instructors





            DRC Exam Proctoring Form for Instructors
          Heading link



 
Copy link



This form is for Instructors whose student(s) will be taking their exam(s) at the DRC.
Exams WILL NOT be administered without this form.



Name(s) of student(s) taking the exam (please list all students in class with submitted LOAs) *  RequiredIf a student requests to take an exam for this course at the DRC and their name is not listed above: *  RequiredPlease administer the exam to the studentPlease contact professor first for approvalDo not administer the exam to the studentInstructor Name (If multiple instructors, please list all) *  RequiredTeaching Assistant Name (if applicable)Course Name and Number (e.g. ACTG 210) *  RequiredCourse CRNIf multiple sections of this course are offered, please provide course CRN.Instructor Phone Number *  RequiredInstructor UIC Email Address *  Required

Preferred Method of Contact *  RequiredPhoneEmailTestsYou may list multiple exam dates by clicking the + symbol to the right of the entry boxes, if you would like the same proctor form to be used all semester.Test NumberTest DateHow much time is the class given to complete the exam?   QuizzesYou may list multiple quiz dates by clicking the + symbol to the right of the entry boxes, if you would like the same proctor form to be used all semester.Quiz NumberQuiz DateHow much time is the class given to complete this quiz?   When can the student take the test/quiz? *  Required

Student must take test/quiz on the day and time as class


Student may take test/quiz at any time on same day as class


Student may take test on another day per written instructor approval.
